BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:light-work-artist-in-residence-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260524T083649Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260701
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260702
SUMMARY:Deadline: Light Work Artist-in-Residence 2027 (Syracuse\, NY)
DESCRIPTION:Light Work\, an independent non-profit founded in 1973\, offers
  a long-running artist-in-residence programme dedicated to the development
  of experimental and contemporary photographic practices. Over 400 artists
  have participated in the residency\, with many going on to gain internati
 onal recognition. ELIGIBILITY: artists working in photography or image-bas
 ed media\, from any country and at any career stage. Apply via the Light W
 ork SlideRoom portal.\n\nOrganisation: Light Work\nLocation: Syracuse\, Ne
 w York\, USA (in-person\, one-month residency on site)\nAward: $7\,500 sti
 pend plus a furnished apartment and access to state-of-the-art photography
  facilities. The residency concludes with a feature in a special edition o
 f 'Contact Sheet: The Light Work Annual' alongside a commissioned essay. N
 o application fee.\nDuration: One-month residency in 2027\n\nMore: https:/
 /lightwork.slideroom.com
URL:https://lightwork.slideroom.com
LOCATION:Syracuse\, New York\, USA (in-person\, one-month residency on site
 )
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:the-lab-living-wage-residencies-2026-27@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260524T083649Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260531
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260601
SUMMARY:Deadline: The Lab: Living Wage Residencies 2026-27 (San Francisco)
DESCRIPTION:The Lab's flagship Living Wage Residency\, a substantial in-per
 son residency in San Francisco's Mission District for artists working in a
 ny media and discipline. Since 2014 the programme has directed over USD 1 
 million to artists\, with artist fees representing nearly 30% of The Lab's
  average operating budget. The Lab's history is as a site for experimental
  and interdisciplinary work spanning performance\, exhibition\, installati
 on\, sound and experimental music\, writing\, institutional critique\, soc
 ial practice\, parades\, feasts and further disciplines yet to be defined.
  The Lab's mission centres traditionally underrepresented artists\, partic
 ularly those identifying as BIPOC\, LGBTQ+\, women\, disabled and/or from 
 economically marginalised backgrounds. ELIGIBILITY: artists based in the S
 an Francisco Bay Area (tight geographic restriction\; in-person access to 
 The Lab's space is central to the residency). SUPPORT per residency: USD 1
 7\,530 artist fee (3 months at a Bay Area living wage per MIT's Living Wag
 e Calculator)\; USD 5\,000 for collaborators and materials\; three months 
 of rehearsal/workshop access to The Lab's space (as available around other
  programming)\; two weeks of continuous use of the exhibition and performa
 nce spaces\; curatorial and marketing support\, outside studio visits\, do
 cumentation and publicity. PROCESS: Stage 1 application (CV\, 3 work links
 \, brief project description and resource plan) due 31 May 2026\; Stage 2 
 invites up to 12 selected artists to develop a full proposal with a USD 25
 0 stipend (Stage 2 deadline TBD). Reviewed by a diverse panel of professio
 nal artists and curators plus The Lab's Board. Outside funding additionall
 y secured for a proposal is not factored into the decision\, but The Lab m
 ay help identify further sources. Supported by the San Francisco Arts Comm
 ission.\n\nOrganisation: The Lab\nLocation: San Francisco Bay Area\, Calif
 ornia\, USA (eligibility restricted to artists based in the Bay Area\; sig
 nificant in-person access to The Lab's space in the Mission District is re
 quired)\nAward: USD 17\,530 artist fee per resident (commensurate with thr
 ee months of work at a San Francisco Bay Area living wage per MIT's Living
  Wage Calculator) plus USD 5\,000 for collaborators and materials. Three m
 onths of rehearsal/workshop access to The Lab's space\, plus two weeks of 
 continuous use of the exhibition and performance spaces for the residency 
 outcome. Curatorial and marketing support\, outside studio visits\, docume
 ntation and publicity. Stage-2 finalists receive an additional USD 250 sti
 pend to develop their full proposal. No application fee.\nDuration: Reside
 ncies take place between July 2026 and June 2027\n\nMore: https://www.thel
 ab.org/
URL:https://www.thelab.org/
LOCATION:San Francisco Bay Area\, California\, USA (eligibility restricted 
 to artists based in the Bay Area\; significant in-person access to The Lab
 's space in the Mission District is required)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:headlands-air-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260524T083649Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260601
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260602
SUMMARY:Deadline: Headlands Center for the Arts: Artist in Residence 2027 (
 AIR)
DESCRIPTION:Open call for the 2027 cohort of the Headlands Artist in Reside
 nce (AIR) program\, one of the longer-running fully-sponsored residencies 
 on the US West Coast. Approximately 50 local\, national and international 
 artists are selected each year for a residency of 4 to 10 weeks at the Hea
 dlands' Marin Headlands campus (former military buildings inside the Golde
 n Gate National Recreation Area\, just north of San Francisco). Residents 
 receive a private studio\, chef-prepared meals\, on-site housing\, travel 
 costs\, and a living-expense stipend\, fully sponsored by the program. Ope
 n to artists at all career stages working in any medium: drawing\, paintin
 g\, sculpture\, photography\, film\, video\, new media\, installation\, fi
 ction and nonfiction writing\, poetry\, dance\, music\, interdisciplinary 
 practice\, social practice\, and architecture. Strong fit for new-media / 
 interdisciplinary / research-driven practices. Application opens 1 April 2
 026 and closes 1 June 2026 via SlideRoom\; applicants are notified of deci
 sions by 11 December 2026. Free to apply.\n\nOrganisation: Headlands Cente
 r for the Arts\nLocation: Sausalito\, California\, United States (Marin He
 adlands\, Golden Gate National Recreation Area)\nAward: Fully sponsored re
 sidency: studio space\, chef-prepared meals\, on-site housing\, travel cos
 ts\, and living-expense stipend. No application fee.\nDuration: 4 to 10 we
 eks\, scheduled between January and December 2027\n\nMore: https://www.hea
 dlands.org/program/air/
URL:https://www.headlands.org/program/air/
LOCATION:Sausalito\, California\, United States (Marin Headlands\, Golden G
 ate National Recreation Area)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:third-wave-fund-artist-in-residence-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260524T083649Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260513
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260514
SUMMARY:Deadline: Third Wave Fund: Artist-in-Residence Program 2026
DESCRIPTION:Annual paid virtual residency for one emerging visual artist wi
 th skills in digital illustration and light animation\, supporting Third W
 ave Fund's gender-justice and liberation visibility\, fundraising and dono
 r mobilisation. Deliverables in 2026: two digital illustrations and one sh
 ort-form animated reel for storytelling and fundraising. Five-month reside
 ncy with a $10\,000 stipend\, mentorship and guidance from long-time movem
 ent artists\, feedback sessions\, experience and portfolio building\, and 
 social-media spotlight opportunities. Eligibility: 18+\; valid SSN or EIN\
 ; currently residing in the US or US Territories\; emerging visual artist 
 (early career\, generally up to 10 years of practice\; no degree-granting 
 art-school enrolment)\; skilled in digital illustration and light animatio
 n\; available for the full schedule. Schedule: orientation 14 July 2026\; 
 project meetings 21 July\, 16 September\, 4 November\; mentoring session 1
 4 October\; debrief 10 December 2026. TWF is a fully remote organisation o
 perating a 4-day work week (Monday to Thursday)\; all communications and m
 eetings happen Mon-Thu via Zoom and email. Deadline 13 May 2026 at 17:00 C
 ST. Notifications go out in the first week of June 2026. Questions: comms@
 thirdwavefund.org (response within ~3 Mon-Thu business days).\n\nOrganisat
 ion: Third Wave Fund\nLocation: Remote (must be currently residing in the 
 United States or US Territories\; valid SSN or EIN required)\nAward: $10\,
 000 stipend\nDuration: 5 months (13 July 2026 to 10 December 2026)\n\nMore
 : https://www.thirdwavefund.org/third-wave-funds-artist-in-residence-progr
 am
URL:https://www.thirdwavefund.org/third-wave-funds-artist-in-residence-prog
 ram
LOCATION:Remote (must be currently residing in the United States or US Terr
 itories\; valid SSN or EIN required)
END:VEVENT
